news.title: Goa hikes stamp duty for transfer of property registration
news.para: The revenue department said that it aims to “reduce the stamp duty chargeable on conveyance”, but the conveyance charges have actually become more expensive, said builders.

news.title: Gurugram: Fire officials took bribe to certify five towers of Orris Aster Court Premier as safe
news.para: The MCG began the probe after a group of residents of the society approached the chief minister with a complaint against then assistant divisional fire officer (ADFO) Satyawan Samriwal in June last year.

news.title: Homebuyer approaches NCRDC against Karnataka-RERA order
news.para: Dhananjaya Padmanabhachar, the complainant, said that he had booked a flat in Mantri Serenity Apartment in 2013 with a delivery commitment of 2016 but the builder did not deliver the flat with undivided share of interest in the project.

news.title: YEIDA seized back plots from 14 builders in three years over delays & dues
news.para: ​The Authority also forfeited over Rs 209 crore of developers who had been allotted over 15.25 lakh sqm of land altogether, officials said.

news.title: Haryana RERA asks ILD to refund homebuyer's money with interest
news.para: The complainant booked an apartment in ILD Arete group housing project on June 10, 2015 and the due date of possession was December 10, 2019.

news.title: SBI home loan book tops Rs 6 lakh crore mark
news.para: ​To mark the occasion, the bank also announced a festive offer for home loan buyers, offering up to 25 bps discount on interest rate starting at 8.40 per cent and also the waiver of the processing fee till January 31, 2023.

news.title: Delhi civic body wants C&D waste from landfill sites to be used in construction activities
news.para: He said that it has been decided that any department, agency, individual or contractor can take the C&D and inert material for their use themselves, free of cost from these three landfill sites -- Bhalaswa, Ghazipur and Okhla.

news.title: Kolhapur civic body's two-day camp to clear building proposals from Oct 13
news.para: All applications, for plot sizes less than 1,000 square metre, that were submitted manually before the mandatory online application process was streamlined will be put up for clearance.

news.title: Nagpur: Lendi Talao to shrink from 29 acres to seven after revival
news.para: The Nagpur Municipal Corporation (NMC) had submitted detailed project report (DPR) of the two lakes to Maharashtra Jeevan Pradhikaran (MJP), agency appointed by the state for technical scrutiny, and obtained sanction.

news.title: Indore: 65 buildings between Jinsi & Lakshmibai Pratima to be trimmed for road widening
news.para: Indore Municipal Corporation (IMC) officials said that they have started issuing notices in the name of the residents whose constructions are located on this stretch.

news.title: Houses on government land will be razed: Goa CM
news.para: “If anyone is found to have illegally built and sold houses in government land, then their structures will be demolished immediately,” Sawant said.

news.title: Gurugram: Soon, Vipul World to get new power connections
news.para: DHBVN had also asked the developer of the project to submit the bank guarantee and hand over 500 square yards of land for constructing a 33kV substation.

news.title: Sanjaynagar scheme among biggest in India under PMAY: Vadodara Mayor
news.para: The Sanjaynagar housing scheme for the urban poor under the Pradhan Mantri Aavas Yojana (PMAY) is now being touted to be amongst the biggest of its kind in the country. Work on the scheme formally began after a long delay on Monday.

news.title: Nashik civic body makes names of 600 big property tax defaulters public
news.para: The civic body has uploaded the list of the defaulters on its official website and requested them to clear their dues at the earliest. These 600 defaulters owe over Rs 40 crore to the civic body — ranging from Rs 1 lakh to over Rs 20 lakh each.

news.title: Dehradun civic body sends notices to 10,000 property tax defaulters
news.para: The scrutiny is still on and as more wards are covered, more defaulters may be identified soon, DMC officials said, adding that if they fail to make payment, they will be penalised.
